<paragraph id="8BCC2241B63AFF85CDA4FE8BFDF414BF" blockId="2.[166,1224,263,673]" lastBlockId="4.[166,1225,1387,1830]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
S h o r t d e s c r i p t i o n. Head matt brown, with black occiput and antenna; frons opaque reddish, deeply shagreened, narrowest part in male about 0.2, in female about 0.5 as wide as eye, vertex shagreened, subshining, setae and setulae black, one orbital seta at posterior one-third; ocellar triangle and orbital plates almost inconspicuous; frons and parafacial sparsely setulose. Antenna, including arista, black, all segments densely covered with scales, matt; scape with one row of setulae; pedicel with 1–2 rows of setulae and one long seta dorsally of pedicellar notch; flagellomere 1 rounded, as long as wide; arista 3-segmented, conspicuously microtrichose (
<figureCitation id="13483EC4B63AFF83CEC5FE6BFBE61078" box="[954,1082,486,513]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[178,211,1458,1480]" captionTargetBox="[204,1187,174,1426]" captionTargetId="figure-106@3.[201,1191,174,1436]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig.8–15.Prodalmannia variabilis, SEM photographs:8–10 —head (8 — anterior, 9 — posterior, 10 — anterior view); 11 — antenna, dorsal; 12 — same, base of arista; 13 — vertex and frons; 14 — face vestiture; 15 — apicoventral comb of oviscape." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453490" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453490/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">fig. 11–12</figureCitation>
). Parafacial brownish-yellow, with subshining triangle; gena opaque reddish brown, soft, wider than vertical diameter of eye and 0.7–0.8 times as high as vertical diameter of eye. Face reddish, matt; antennal grooves widely fused, matt; epistome with black spot dorsally and two black lines along lateral margins. Palpus black, black setose; proboscis blackish, with black hairs. Thorax brownish yellow, shining, with paler postpronotal lobe and pleuron, long black setulose; mesonotum with black marking, short and narrow in female (
<figureCitation id="13483EC4B63BFF82CC4AF9C1FEAA1411" box="[309,374,1613,1640]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[168,201,1793,1815]" captionTargetBox="[280,1132,679,1768]" captionTargetId="figure-214@2.[262,1136,674,1776]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1–7.Prodalmannia variabilis: ♀ (1, 6), Ò (2–5) and its possible host, Phyllotocus macleayi (7): 1 — habitus, antero-dorsal; 2, 7 — same, dorsal; 3 —same, lateral; 4 — head, anterior; 5 — wing; 6 — oviscape." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453488/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">fig. 1</figureCitation>
), sometimes entirely lacking, and wider and longer in male (
<figureCitation id="13483EC4B63BFF82C903F9C1FB1D1411" box="[1148,1217,1613,1640]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[168,201,1793,1815]" captionTargetBox="[280,1132,679,1768]" captionTargetId="figure-214@2.[262,1136,674,1776]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1–7.Prodalmannia variabilis: ♀ (1, 6), Ò (2–5) and its possible host, Phyllotocus macleayi (7): 1 — habitus, antero-dorsal; 2, 7 — same, dorsal; 3 —same, lateral; 4 — head, anterior; 5 — wing; 6 — oviscape." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453488/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">fig. 2</figureCitation>
), with 1 postpronotal, 1 presutural supra-alar, 2 dorsocentral and 1 presutural acrostichal seta present; scutellum entirely subshining brownish yellow, with 3–4 pairs of long marginal setae and additional setulae, but mostly bare on disk; katepisternum and meron usually with black marks; mediotergite shining black. Wings hyaline, greyish microtrichose; yellowish at bases and on costa, veins yellowish, darkened on distal half of wing. Halteres pale yellowish. Legs brownish yellow, black setose and setulose, with apically darkened tibiae and brownish-black tarsi. Abdomen shining brownish yellow, long black setulose. Male genitalia as on 
<figureCitation id="13483EC4B63CFF85CE4BFA07FC6F17DC" box="[820,947,1419,1445]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[170,203,1209,1231]" captionTargetBox="[300,1093,174,1161]" captionTargetId="figure-185@4.[297,1097,162,1163]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 16–22. Prodalmannia variabilis, Ò genitalia: 16 — epandrium posterior; 17–18 — epandrium and hypandrium, right lateral (17) and ventral (18) view; 19 — basiphallus; 20 — glans of phallus; 21–22 — ejaculatory apodeme, lateral and ventral. Ab b re v i at i o n s: basph — basiphallus; hypd — hypandrium; phapod — phallapodeme; pregt — pregonite; prens — prensisetae; sf — sensillar field; sur — surstylus; va ap — vanes of apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453494" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453494/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">fig. 16–22</figureCitation>
: epandrium short and rounded, dorsally densely setulose, with short outer surstyli; inner surstylus with row of setulae and 2–4 prensisetae (
<figureCitation id="13483EC4B63CFF85CF50FA47FD6C179F" box="[559,688,1483,1510]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[170,203,1209,1231]" captionTargetBox="[300,1093,174,1161]" captionTargetId="figure-185@4.[297,1097,162,1163]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 16–22. Prodalmannia variabilis, Ò genitalia: 16 — epandrium posterior; 17–18 — epandrium and hypandrium, right lateral (17) and ventral (18) view; 19 — basiphallus; 20 — glans of phallus; 21–22 — ejaculatory apodeme, lateral and ventral. Ab b re v i at i o n s: basph — basiphallus; hypd — hypandrium; phapod — phallapodeme; pregt — pregonite; prens — prensisetae; sf — sensillar field; sur — surstylus; va ap — vanes of apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453494" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453494/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">fig. 16, 18</figureCitation>
); hypandrium with widely separated vanes connected to equal paired pregonites (
<figureCitation id="13483EC4B63CFF85CFF6FA67FCD6147F" box="[649,778,1515,1542]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[170,203,1209,1231]" captionTargetBox="[300,1093,174,1161]" captionTargetId="figure-185@4.[297,1097,162,1163]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 16–22. Prodalmannia variabilis, Ò genitalia: 16 — epandrium posterior; 17–18 — epandrium and hypandrium, right lateral (17) and ventral (18) view; 19 — basiphallus; 20 — glans of phallus; 21–22 — ejaculatory apodeme, lateral and ventral. Ab b re v i at i o n s: basph — basiphallus; hypd — hypandrium; phapod — phallapodeme; pregt — pregonite; prens — prensisetae; sf — sensillar field; sur — surstylus; va ap — vanes of apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453494" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453494/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">fig. 17–18</figureCitation>
); sensillar fields (remnants of postgonites) allied to basiphallus present; border of basiphallus and subepandrial sclerite with fold covered by ciliae or microtrichia (
<figureCitation id="13483EC4B63CFF85CF86F9A7FC90143F" box="[761,844,1579,1606]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[170,203,1209,1231]" captionTargetBox="[300,1093,174,1161]" captionTargetId="figure-185@4.[297,1097,162,1163]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 16–22. Prodalmannia variabilis, Ò genitalia: 16 — epandrium posterior; 17–18 — epandrium and hypandrium, right lateral (17) and ventral (18) view; 19 — basiphallus; 20 — glans of phallus; 21–22 — ejaculatory apodeme, lateral and ventral. Ab b re v i at i o n s: basph — basiphallus; hypd — hypandrium; phapod — phallapodeme; pregt — pregonite; prens — prensisetae; sf — sensillar field; sur — surstylus; va ap — vanes of apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453494" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453494/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">fig. 19</figureCitation>
); phallus bare, with short and very poorly sclerotized glans (
<figureCitation id="13483EC4B63CFF85CF5DF9C7FDAA141F" box="[546,630,1611,1638]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[170,203,1209,1231]" captionTargetBox="[300,1093,174,1161]" captionTargetId="figure-185@4.[297,1097,162,1163]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 16–22. Prodalmannia variabilis, Ò genitalia: 16 — epandrium posterior; 17–18 — epandrium and hypandrium, right lateral (17) and ventral (18) view; 19 — basiphallus; 20 — glans of phallus; 21–22 — ejaculatory apodeme, lateral and ventral. Ab b re v i at i o n s: basph — basiphallus; hypd — hypandrium; phapod — phallapodeme; pregt — pregonite; prens — prensisetae; sf — sensillar field; sur — surstylus; va ap — vanes of apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453494" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453494/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">fig. 20</figureCitation>
); ejaculatory apodeme fan-like, with very large sperm pump (
<figureCitation id="13483EC4B63CFF85CC2BF9E7FE0A14FF" box="[340,470,1643,1670]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[170,203,1209,1231]" captionTargetBox="[300,1093,174,1161]" captionTargetId="figure-185@4.[297,1097,162,1163]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 16–22. Prodalmannia variabilis, Ò genitalia: 16 — epandrium posterior; 17–18 — epandrium and hypandrium, right lateral (17) and ventral (18) view; 19 — basiphallus; 20 — glans of phallus; 21–22 — ejaculatory apodeme, lateral and ventral. Ab b re v i at i o n s: basph — basiphallus; hypd — hypandrium; phapod — phallapodeme; pregt — pregonite; prens — prensisetae; sf — sensillar field; sur — surstylus; va ap — vanes of apodeme." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453494" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453494/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">fig. 20–21</figureCitation>
). Female sternites 3–6 transverse, setulose (
<figureCitation id="13483EC4B63CFF85CE8CF9E7FB9A14FF" box="[1011,1094,1643,1670]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[175,208,1113,1135]" captionTargetBox="[265,1176,204,1081]" captionTargetId="figure-214@5.[255,1176,196,1081]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 23–29. Prodalmannia variabilis, ♀ genitalia: 23 — abdomen, ventral view; 24 — eversible membranev ventral; 25 — eversible memrane and aculeus, lateral (left) view; 26 — aculeus; 27 — same, cercal unit, enlarged; 28 — ventral receptacle; 29 — spermathecae. Ab b re v i at i on s: an — anal opening; cer — cercal unit; st8 — 8th sternite; tae — taenia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453496" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453496/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">fig. 23</figureCitation>
); terminalia: oviscape very wide, shining black (
<figureCitation id="13483EC4B63CFF85CFF4F907FD1314DF" box="[651,719,1675,1702]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[168,201,1793,1815]" captionTargetBox="[280,1132,679,1768]" captionTargetId="figure-214@2.[262,1136,674,1776]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1–7.Prodalmannia variabilis: ♀ (1, 6), Ò (2–5) and its possible host, Phyllotocus macleayi (7): 1 — habitus, antero-dorsal; 2, 7 — same, dorsal; 3 —same, lateral; 4 — head, anterior; 5 — wing; 6 — oviscape." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453488/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">fig. 6</figureCitation>
); ventrally with tongue-like flap formed by 9–10 thick setae (
<figureCitation id="13483EC4B63CFF85CCD4F927FE3014BC" box="[427,492,1707,1733]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[168,201,1793,1815]" captionTargetBox="[280,1132,679,1768]" captionTargetId="figure-214@2.[262,1136,674,1776]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1–7.Prodalmannia variabilis: ♀ (1, 6), Ò (2–5) and its possible host, Phyllotocus macleayi (7): 1 — habitus, antero-dorsal; 2, 7 — same, dorsal; 3 —same, lateral; 4 — head, anterior; 5 — wing; 6 — oviscape." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453488/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">fig. 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13483EC4B63CFF85CC85F927FDC614BF" box="[506,538,1707,1734]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[178,211,1458,1480]" captionTargetBox="[204,1187,174,1426]" captionTargetId="figure-106@3.[201,1191,174,1436]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig.8–15.Prodalmannia variabilis, SEM photographs:8–10 —head (8 — anterior, 9 — posterior, 10 — anterior view); 11 — antenna, dorsal; 12 — same, base of arista; 13 — vertex and frons; 14 — face vestiture; 15 — apicoventral comb of oviscape." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453490" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453490/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">15</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
